1
00:00:13,767 --> 00:00:15,600
<i> And, are you all ready?</i>

2
00:00:15,733 --> 00:00:19,767
<i> There you go. One, two, three!</i>

3
00:00:19,900 --> 00:00:21,567
<i> Out, everybody! Get out!</i>

4
00:00:21,700 --> 00:00:23,600
<i> The kid! Hurry!</i>

5
00:00:25,067 --> 00:00:27,467
<i> Tetay! Get out now, hurry!</i>

6
00:00:27,600 --> 00:00:29,333
<i> We're not leaving without Mom!</i>

7
00:00:29,467 --> 00:00:31,733
<i>- Where's Mom?
- Come on, get out!</i>

8
00:00:34,767 --> 00:00:36,000
<i> Hazel.</i>

9
00:00:36,133 --> 00:00:37,500
<i> Surprise.</i>

10
00:00:37,633 --> 00:00:38,600
<i> I'm back.</i>

11
00:00:38,733 --> 00:00:40,200
<i> Felma!</i>

12
00:00:40,333 --> 00:00:42,000
<i>Manuel, maybe she's already
outside. Let's go!</i>

13
00:00:42,133 --> 00:00:43,400
<i> Let go of me! Help!</i>

14
00:00:43,533 --> 00:00:46,867
<i>Go on, try it.
I'll slit your throat.</i>

15
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:49,000
<i> Where's Mom?</i>

16
00:00:49,133 --> 00:00:50,333
<i> She's not here yet?</i>

17
00:00:50,467 --> 00:00:51,867
<i> Mom isn't here.</i>

18
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:53,633
<i>- What?
- Where's Mom?</i>

19
00:00:53,767 --> 00:00:55,233
<i> Felma!</i>

20
00:00:55,367 --> 00:00:56,500
<i> Help!</i>

21
00:01:00,833 --> 00:01:01,700
<i> Hello?</i>

22
00:01:01,833 --> 00:01:03,033
<i> Hello, Manuel.</i>

23
00:01:03,167 --> 00:01:05,333
<i> Felma, my love. Where are you?</i>

24
00:01:05,467 --> 00:01:07,500
<i> Hey! What's that, huh?</i>

25
00:01:07,667 --> 00:01:08,867
<i>- Manuel!
- What are you doing?</i>

26
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:10,333
<i>- What is that?
- Manuel!</i>

27
00:01:10,467 --> 00:01:11,700
<i> Hello, love?</i>

28
00:01:14,733 --> 00:01:17,400
<i> I'll kill you! You monster!</i>

29
00:01:17,533 --> 00:01:19,567
<i>I just spoke
with Colonel Sarabia.</i>

30
00:01:20,667 --> 00:01:23,600
<i>He said Hazel escaped
two days ago.</i>

31
00:01:26,533 --> 00:01:28,167
<i> Men...</i>

32
00:01:28,300 --> 00:01:29,967
<i> secure the perimeter!</i>

33
00:01:30,100 --> 00:01:32,567
<i>Quietly move the guests
to the safe area.</i>

34
00:01:32,700 --> 00:01:35,633
<i>I want eyes on every corner
of this resort!</i>

35
00:01:35,767 --> 00:01:38,300
<i>- You understand?
- Sir, yes, Sir!</i>

36
00:01:38,433 --> 00:01:40,600
<i> Drone up in 60. Move!</i>

37
00:01:45,267 --> 00:01:47,667
Yes, I'm still here. Room 206!

38
00:01:47,800 --> 00:01:49,800
You keep asking!

39
00:01:49,933 --> 00:01:52,467
Come on, hurry up!
Just be careful.

40
00:01:55,633 --> 00:01:58,200
Will we see each other, my love?

41
00:01:59,700 --> 00:02:02,167
<i> Is this place nice?</i>

42
00:02:02,300 --> 00:02:03,600
<i> Yeah, it's beautiful.</i>

43
00:02:04,933 --> 00:02:08,800
<i>But wait, we don't really
have anything coming up.</i>

44
00:02:10,467 --> 00:02:12,667
<i> Come on. Sit down first.</i>

45
00:02:12,800 --> 00:02:14,133
<i> Thank you.</i>

46
00:02:21,567 --> 00:02:22,900
<i> FMP staff?</i>

47
00:02:31,700 --> 00:02:33,367
<i> Wait, what's going on?</i>

48
00:02:33,500 --> 00:02:34,500
<i> Felma!</i>

49
00:02:34,633 --> 00:02:35,500
<i> Paz!</i>

50
00:02:35,633 --> 00:02:37,800
<i> Didang!</i>

51
00:02:37,933 --> 00:02:40,400
<i> Even Noah's here!</i>

52
00:02:40,533 --> 00:02:43,033
<i>Wait, what is this?
What's happening?</i>

53
00:02:51,567 --> 00:02:54,133
<i>- Didang really went all out.
- Hi, Mom!</i>

54
00:02:54,267 --> 00:02:55,967
<i> My kids!</i>

55
00:02:56,100 --> 00:02:57,467
<i> What is this?</i>

56
00:02:57,600 --> 00:02:58,800
<i> Wait...</i>

57
00:03:01,467 --> 00:03:04,000
<i>Don't tell me you're dancing,
too?</i>

58
00:03:05,967 --> 00:03:07,300
<i> Felma, I'm single now.</i>

59
00:03:18,067 --> 00:03:21,267
<i> Will you marry me next month?</i>

60
00:03:21,433 --> 00:03:22,667
<i> What?</i>

61
00:03:22,800 --> 00:03:25,467
<i> Wait, next month?</i>

62
00:03:25,600 --> 00:03:29,933
<i>Do you have any idea how hard
it is to plan a wedding?</i>

63
00:03:30,067 --> 00:03:32,300
<i> Oh, Mom, it's all planned.</i>

64
00:03:32,433 --> 00:03:36,067
<i>We've been working on this
for almost ten months.</i>

65
00:03:37,333 --> 00:03:40,633
<i>We were just waiting for
the annulment to be approved.</i>

66
00:03:40,767 --> 00:03:42,833
<i> Yeah, Felma.</i>

67
00:03:42,967 --> 00:03:44,267
<i>Everything's ready.
We have a date, a venue.</i>

68
00:03:45,600 --> 00:03:48,900
<i>Didn't you say
you liked this place?</i>

69
00:03:49,033 --> 00:03:50,700
<i>And you already have
a wedding dress, Mom.</i>

70
00:03:50,833 --> 00:03:53,367
<i>Coleen and I picked it
ourselves. It's all set.</i>

71
00:03:54,733 --> 00:03:56,000
<i>There's just one thing missing.</i>

72
00:03:57,433 --> 00:04:00,000
<i> Your yes.</i>

73
00:04:00,133 --> 00:04:01,900
<i>She hasn't answered yet!
She hasn't answered!</i>

74
00:04:02,033 --> 00:04:03,333
<i> There, there!</i>

75
00:04:05,333 --> 00:04:06,700
<i> Yes, Manuel.</i>

76
00:04:12,333 --> 00:04:14,567
<i>We're getting married
next month!</i>

77
00:04:19,567 --> 00:04:21,667
<i>- Kiss!
- Kiss!</i>

78
00:04:25,467 --> 00:04:28,000
I won't lose to you, Hazel.

79
00:04:29,667 --> 00:04:31,433
No.

80
00:04:31,567 --> 00:04:34,000
What? Are you close?

81
00:04:34,133 --> 00:04:35,467
Hurry up!

82
00:04:49,700 --> 00:04:52,200
Help!
Please help my grandmother!

83
00:04:52,333 --> 00:04:55,067
Sir, please.
She won't come out!

84
00:04:55,200 --> 00:04:56,267
She's scared of the fire!

85
00:04:56,400 --> 00:04:58,800
The fire's been out for a while!
Come down now!

86
00:05:13,200 --> 00:05:15,367
Where are you now?
What's your ETA?

87
00:05:19,600 --> 00:05:21,633
Are we doing nothing?

88
00:05:21,767 --> 00:05:23,600
Why don't we help look for them?

89
00:05:24,667 --> 00:05:26,700
Bro,
maybe we should look around.

90
00:05:26,833 --> 00:05:29,400
Felma and Hazel
might not be inside.

91
00:05:32,767 --> 00:05:34,000
No.

92
00:05:34,167 --> 00:05:36,300
Let the authorities
handle it.

93
00:05:36,433 --> 00:05:38,200
We'll just get in the way.

94
00:05:47,667 --> 00:05:49,067
Sir, what's going on?

95
00:05:49,200 --> 00:05:51,467
You need to evacuate.
Let's go!

96
00:05:57,400 --> 00:05:59,933
What are you smirking at, huh?

97
00:06:00,067 --> 00:06:02,233
What are you smiling about?

98
00:06:02,367 --> 00:06:03,667
Hey!

99
00:06:08,067 --> 00:06:10,133
- Manuel!
- Hey!

100
00:06:10,267 --> 00:06:11,900
Manuel, I'm on the second floor!

101
00:06:12,033 --> 00:06:13,200
- Love!
- Mom?

102
00:06:13,333 --> 00:06:14,367
Ma'am!

103
00:06:15,467 --> 00:06:17,467
Sir, confirmed! The target's
in the other building!

104
00:06:17,600 --> 00:06:18,567
There's a commotion over there.

105
00:06:19,600 --> 00:06:21,600
All units! Stand by.
Target acquired.

106
00:06:21,733 --> 00:06:22,967
Move, move, move!

107
00:06:23,100 --> 00:06:24,433
- Felma!
- Help!

108
00:06:24,567 --> 00:06:26,900
Manuel, I'm on the second floor!

109
00:06:37,333 --> 00:06:39,033
I won't lose to you!

110
00:06:39,167 --> 00:06:41,867
I'll never lose to you!

111
00:06:47,067 --> 00:06:47,933
Manuel!

112
00:06:48,067 --> 00:06:49,967
That's where Mom's screams
are coming from!

113
00:06:54,767 --> 00:06:56,500
Bravo, take them!
Bring them over there!

114
00:06:56,633 --> 00:06:58,867
- Mom!
- Felma!

115
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:00,333
Manuel!

116
00:07:04,100 --> 00:07:05,433
Bravo, Bravo, where are you?

117
00:07:05,567 --> 00:07:06,700
Mom!

118
00:07:14,867 --> 00:07:16,300
Hazel, let Felma go!

119
00:07:16,433 --> 00:07:17,467
Mom!

120
00:07:20,833 --> 00:07:22,467
Why are there cops here, huh?

121
00:07:22,600 --> 00:07:24,167
Obviously,

122
00:07:24,300 --> 00:07:26,400
my husband called them!

123
00:07:26,533 --> 00:07:29,133
They're here to save me.
So let me go!

124
00:07:29,267 --> 00:07:31,200
- You're finished!
- No!

125
00:07:31,333 --> 00:07:32,300
I won't let go!

126
00:07:32,433 --> 00:07:35,067
As long as I have you,
they can't do anything!

127
00:07:35,200 --> 00:07:36,067
You animal!

128
00:07:38,533 --> 00:07:39,700
Where is she?

129
00:07:39,833 --> 00:07:41,033
<i> No clean shot, sir!</i>

130
00:07:41,167 --> 00:07:42,700
The suspect keeps moving!

131
00:07:42,833 --> 00:07:44,400
We can breach the room!

132
00:07:44,533 --> 00:07:47,633
Negative. Insert a low-profile
optic at the threshold.

133
00:07:47,800 --> 00:07:49,033
I need live visuals.

134
00:07:49,167 --> 00:07:51,933
Hostage's condition,
suspect's movement, and weapons.

135
00:07:52,067 --> 00:07:53,267
Report everything to me.

136
00:07:53,400 --> 00:07:55,533
Do not go in unless I say so.

137
00:07:56,833 --> 00:07:58,967
Colonel,
why didn't you approve it?

138
00:07:59,100 --> 00:08:00,833
It's too risky, Manuel.

139
00:08:00,967 --> 00:08:02,967
Hazel could be armed.

140
00:08:03,100 --> 00:08:04,800
She could kill Felma
if we rush in.

141
00:08:06,167 --> 00:08:09,233
What she needs right now
is someone to talk to.

142
00:08:13,733 --> 00:08:15,033
And that's where I come in.

143
00:08:19,267 --> 00:08:21,467
Sir, reporting for duty.

144
00:08:27,267 --> 00:08:29,800
Meet Police Captain
Antonette Ferrer.

145
00:08:29,933 --> 00:08:31,933
Lead Negotiations Officer.

146
00:08:32,067 --> 00:08:33,267
She's a solid,
excellent negotiator.

147
00:08:33,400 --> 00:08:35,067
She's my protégé.

148
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:36,867
High success rate.

149
00:08:39,833 --> 00:08:42,933
Sir, please brief me
on the suspect's profile.

150
00:08:43,067 --> 00:08:43,967
Relationship.

151
00:08:44,100 --> 00:08:45,700
Triggers.

152
00:08:45,833 --> 00:08:47,433
The hostage-taker...

153
00:08:47,567 --> 00:08:48,900
Manuel's ex-wife...

154
00:08:49,033 --> 00:08:50,367
Hazel.

155
00:08:50,500 --> 00:08:53,033
The hostage is his current wife,

156
00:08:53,167 --> 00:08:54,433
Felma.

157
00:09:30,500 --> 00:09:32,200
Alonso, answer it.

158
00:09:34,100 --> 00:09:35,167
<i> We're sorry...</i>

159
00:09:35,300 --> 00:09:36,567
Stop this already.

160
00:09:37,867 --> 00:09:39,433
Turn yourself in.

161
00:09:39,567 --> 00:09:41,600
What are you talking about?

162
00:09:41,733 --> 00:09:43,733
Who am I supposed
to surrender to?

163
00:09:43,867 --> 00:09:46,467
Go back to that hell? No!

164
00:09:46,600 --> 00:09:47,900
You don't have anyone left.

165
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:50,767
They've all turned
their backs on you.

166
00:10:08,933 --> 00:10:12,600
Based on your accounts
and Hazel's records,

167
00:10:12,733 --> 00:10:14,000
the pattern is clear.

168
00:10:15,333 --> 00:10:16,633
Impulsive violence.

169
00:10:17,967 --> 00:10:19,500
Fear-based aggression.

170
00:10:19,633 --> 00:10:21,833
She escalates fast
when cornered.

171
00:10:22,867 --> 00:10:24,200
Do we have eyes?

172
00:10:24,333 --> 00:10:25,667
Still waiting for advice.

173
00:10:27,700 --> 00:10:30,167
Alpha,
where are my drone visuals?

174
00:10:30,300 --> 00:10:32,500
Men, we lost internal visuals.

175
00:10:39,367 --> 00:10:40,600
Patch in the snake cam.

176
00:10:40,733 --> 00:10:42,633
- Copy, sir.
- Snake cam is in.

177
00:10:51,100 --> 00:10:52,300
Why aren't you answering?

178
00:10:52,433 --> 00:10:55,833
This idiot doesn't pick up.
What is he doing?

179
00:10:55,967 --> 00:10:57,600
Don't you have anyone else
to call?

180
00:11:00,133 --> 00:11:03,867
I know two of Hazel's people,
Anton and Nando.

181
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:06,667
Where are Anton and Nando?

182
00:11:10,033 --> 00:11:12,067
<i> They've already been arrested.</i>

183
00:11:12,200 --> 00:11:17,200
They confessed to get lighter
sentences, like Jojo.

184
00:11:17,333 --> 00:11:18,867
What about Alice?

185
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:20,133
Did she leave you, too?

186
00:11:20,267 --> 00:11:21,133
Shut up!

187
00:11:21,267 --> 00:11:22,800
- Shut up!
- Did she leave you, too?

188
00:11:22,933 --> 00:11:23,967
You're really getting
on my nerves!

189
00:11:24,100 --> 00:11:26,567
You won't stop talking!
You've been at it forever!

190
00:11:26,700 --> 00:11:31,867
You won't stop talking!

191
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:34,100
- You animal!
- You're the animal!

192
00:11:42,467 --> 00:11:45,400
- You're a demon, Hazel!
- Dad!

193
00:11:49,933 --> 00:11:50,767
Manuel, don't.

194
00:11:50,900 --> 00:11:53,000
Colonel, my wife is being hurt.

195
00:11:53,133 --> 00:11:54,433
Are we not going to do anything?

196
00:11:54,567 --> 00:11:56,733
Aren't we going to move?

197
00:11:56,867 --> 00:11:58,533
Hazel is cornered.

198
00:11:58,667 --> 00:12:01,533
She's scared. She's desperate.

199
00:12:01,667 --> 00:12:02,800
If she's armed,

200
00:12:02,933 --> 00:12:06,667
one wrong move could trigger
her to kill your wife.

201
00:12:06,800 --> 00:12:08,200
Please, let me handle this.

202
00:12:08,333 --> 00:12:10,633
Manuel, listen to Antonette.

203
00:12:10,767 --> 00:12:12,133
She knows what she's doing.

204
00:12:13,233 --> 00:12:15,000
This is a police operation now.

205
00:12:15,167 --> 00:12:16,467
We'll take it from here.

206
00:12:16,600 --> 00:12:18,333
Move them back.

207
00:12:18,467 --> 00:12:19,867
Move over there, Sir.

208
00:12:23,500 --> 00:12:26,133
What? You want a real fight?

209
00:12:26,267 --> 00:12:27,167
You're actually fighting back?

210
00:12:27,300 --> 00:12:28,467
You can't beat me!

211
00:12:30,333 --> 00:12:32,867
You saw what I did to you,
didn't you?

212
00:12:33,000 --> 00:12:35,200
My inmates taught me
how to fight in there.

213
00:12:35,333 --> 00:12:37,167
You don't stand a chance
against me!

214
00:12:47,767 --> 00:12:49,467
What was the room number again?

215
00:12:49,600 --> 00:12:51,000
Right here, Ma'am.

216
00:12:52,133 --> 00:12:53,500
Thank you.

217
00:12:56,667 --> 00:12:59,233
Because of you,
my life fell apart.

218
00:12:59,367 --> 00:13:00,800
You have no shame.

219
00:13:00,933 --> 00:13:04,900
I'm so fed up with you.
I should really kill you!

220
00:13:05,033 --> 00:13:06,767
I will kill you...

221
00:13:27,467 --> 00:13:28,567
Hello?

222
00:13:28,700 --> 00:13:30,400
Who's this?

223
00:13:30,533 --> 00:13:31,767
<i> Hazel.</i>

224
00:13:31,900 --> 00:13:34,100
This is Police Captain
Antonette Ferrer.

225
00:13:35,867 --> 00:13:37,500
Tell me.

226
00:13:37,633 --> 00:13:39,233
What do you want?

227
00:13:39,367 --> 00:13:41,000
Nothing. I don't need anything.

228
00:13:41,133 --> 00:13:42,800
This is it.
I already have what I need.

229
00:13:42,933 --> 00:13:44,533
What I need is right here.

230
00:13:44,667 --> 00:13:46,300
What are you planning
to do to Felma?

231
00:13:46,433 --> 00:13:48,967
That's none of your business.
Why? Who are you, huh?

232
00:13:49,100 --> 00:13:50,467
It's none of your business!

233
00:13:50,600 --> 00:13:51,533
It is my business.

234
00:13:51,667 --> 00:13:56,100
Her family and friends
are worried about her.

235
00:13:56,267 --> 00:13:57,833
Why?

236
00:13:57,967 --> 00:13:59,933
Does anyone even care about me?

237
00:14:00,067 --> 00:14:02,333
Yes. I do.

238
00:14:02,467 --> 00:14:04,500
Your life matters, Hazel.

239
00:14:05,867 --> 00:14:07,100
That's why I'm worried.

240
00:14:07,233 --> 00:14:10,167
I don't want anything bad
to happen to you in there.

241
00:14:10,300 --> 00:14:11,467
So what are you going to do?

242
00:14:11,600 --> 00:14:13,233
You're going to kill me?

243
00:14:13,367 --> 00:14:14,967
Go ahead and try.

244
00:14:15,100 --> 00:14:16,900
Because I'll make sure
to kill this woman

245
00:14:17,033 --> 00:14:20,633
before you can do that.

246
00:14:20,767 --> 00:14:22,733
You won't see her alive!
Do you understand?

247
00:14:22,867 --> 00:14:25,333
This woman will die first!

248
00:14:25,467 --> 00:14:28,733
Will you feel better
if you kill Felma?

249
00:14:28,900 --> 00:14:30,667
Will the pain disappear?

250
00:14:30,800 --> 00:14:33,300
Yes, because...

251
00:14:33,433 --> 00:14:35,467
Manuel will mourn
for the rest of his life.

252
00:14:35,600 --> 00:14:37,267
He deserves it.

253
00:14:37,400 --> 00:14:39,100
He won't grieve, Hazel.

254
00:14:40,433 --> 00:14:42,533
He and Felma have children.

255
00:14:43,833 --> 00:14:44,967
There are people
who will comfort him.

256
00:14:45,100 --> 00:14:47,733
People who will love him
as he grows old.

257
00:14:49,133 --> 00:14:50,967
I understand you.

258
00:14:51,100 --> 00:14:52,333
You loved.

259
00:14:52,467 --> 00:14:54,533
You got hurt.
Your world fell apart.

260
00:14:56,267 --> 00:14:59,167
But that doesn't mean it's over.

261
00:14:59,300 --> 00:15:02,333
You can still change your life.

262
00:15:02,500 --> 00:15:03,933
What is this?

263
00:15:04,067 --> 00:15:06,833
You monsters!
Are you watching me?

264
00:15:06,967 --> 00:15:08,700
<i>You're spying on me, aren't you?</i>

265
00:15:08,833 --> 00:15:10,367
Take it out! Take it out!

266
00:15:10,500 --> 00:15:12,733
Hazel, calm down.

267
00:15:12,867 --> 00:15:14,033
We'll pull it out.

268
00:15:14,167 --> 00:15:16,767
I'll kill her.
I'll kill this woman!

269
00:15:19,467 --> 00:15:20,800
Delta, withdraw the optic.

270
00:15:20,933 --> 00:15:22,133
Call back now!

271
00:15:22,267 --> 00:15:23,300
Pull out!

272
00:15:40,767 --> 00:15:44,667
Men, we lost internal visuals.

273
00:15:44,800 --> 00:15:47,100
Sir, we still have overwatch.

274
00:15:47,233 --> 00:15:48,933
Put the drone feed full screen.

275
00:15:53,533 --> 00:15:56,300
Felma's arm has blood.

276
00:15:56,433 --> 00:15:58,167
You're evil, Hazel!

277
00:16:02,333 --> 00:16:04,800
Alpha, conceal the drone
from the suspect.

278
00:16:04,933 --> 00:16:06,267
Copy, sir.

279
00:16:27,700 --> 00:16:29,367
Why don't they bring
the drone closer

280
00:16:29,500 --> 00:16:32,400
so we can see
what's happening inside?

281
00:16:33,900 --> 00:16:35,600
Paz...

282
00:16:35,733 --> 00:16:37,867
they're keeping a safe distance.

283
00:16:39,567 --> 00:16:41,267
So Hazel won't notice.

284
00:16:42,800 --> 00:16:44,533
Kids,

285
00:16:44,667 --> 00:16:46,833
I need to get to Room 206.

286
00:16:47,767 --> 00:16:49,333
What?

287
00:16:49,467 --> 00:16:50,700
Dad, don't!

288
00:16:50,833 --> 00:16:52,500
I don't care anymore.

289
00:16:52,633 --> 00:16:53,800
It's already night.

290
00:16:53,933 --> 00:16:56,567
The negotiations
aren't going anywhere.

291
00:16:56,700 --> 00:16:58,933
Hazel's had your mom for hours.

292
00:16:59,067 --> 00:17:01,800
Are we just going to wait?

293
00:17:01,933 --> 00:17:03,200
But, Dad...

294
00:17:03,333 --> 00:17:05,533
I'll save your mother.

295
00:17:05,667 --> 00:17:08,133
Even if it costs me my life.

296
00:17:08,267 --> 00:17:09,867
Stay here.

297
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:11,300
I'll find a way.

298
00:17:33,800 --> 00:17:36,200
Come on, Alonso.

299
00:17:36,333 --> 00:17:37,567
Answer it.

300
00:17:41,667 --> 00:17:44,933
You're out of partners now.

301
00:17:45,067 --> 00:17:47,800
All your accomplices are gone,
Hazel.

302
00:17:47,933 --> 00:17:49,600
They're all gone!

303
00:17:53,333 --> 00:17:55,400
They left you.

304
00:17:56,700 --> 00:17:58,400
Hello, Alonso!

305
00:17:59,800 --> 00:18:01,033
Finally.

306
00:18:01,167 --> 00:18:03,633
Hazel, there was just a problem.

307
00:18:03,767 --> 00:18:05,800
But I'm here now.

308
00:18:05,933 --> 00:18:08,033
I just can't get inside.

309
00:18:08,167 --> 00:18:10,867
- There are cops everywhere.
- It's fine, it's fine.

310
00:18:11,000 --> 00:18:12,800
Help me, okay?

311
00:18:12,933 --> 00:18:14,967
Help me get out of here.

312
00:18:15,100 --> 00:18:16,433
Okay.

313
00:18:17,967 --> 00:18:20,900
But you need to pay me
ten million first.

314
00:18:21,033 --> 00:18:22,467
What?

315
00:18:22,633 --> 00:18:24,967
What the hell are you
talking about?

316
00:18:25,100 --> 00:18:26,633
Just listen.

317
00:18:26,767 --> 00:18:27,933
I have an idea.

318
00:18:29,000 --> 00:18:30,333
All right.

319
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:41,700
Sir, you can't go in there. Sir!

320
00:18:43,033 --> 00:18:45,400
Sir! Sir, wait.

321
00:18:45,533 --> 00:18:47,100
- My wife needs me!
- Go on, go on.

322
00:18:47,233 --> 00:18:49,533
- Sir, wait!
- My wife needs me!

323
00:18:49,667 --> 00:18:51,867
- Go on, take him in.
- Just a second, please!

324
00:18:54,367 --> 00:18:55,533
Wait.

325
00:18:55,700 --> 00:18:57,767
Wait, my wife needs me!

326
00:18:57,900 --> 00:18:58,800
- Wait!
- Dad!

327
00:18:58,933 --> 00:19:00,567
- Colonel!
- Manuel,

328
00:19:00,700 --> 00:19:03,067
you're not the only one
who wants to save Felma.

329
00:19:03,200 --> 00:19:05,567
I do, too.
This is personal for me.

330
00:19:05,700 --> 00:19:08,267
Felma is my friend. So please,

331
00:19:08,400 --> 00:19:12,733
let me do my job
and save my friend.

332
00:19:12,867 --> 00:19:16,867
Colonel, I'm scared of
what Hazel might do to Felma.

333
00:19:17,000 --> 00:19:18,133
I understand.

334
00:19:18,267 --> 00:19:21,500
But do not make a decision that
could compromise my operation.

335
00:19:32,867 --> 00:19:34,933
Hello, Hazel?

336
00:19:35,067 --> 00:19:36,567
Listen to me.

337
00:19:36,700 --> 00:19:38,767
I want a helicopter.

338
00:19:40,033 --> 00:19:43,167
And I want 20 million pesos...

339
00:19:43,300 --> 00:19:44,867
in cash.

340
00:19:45,000 --> 00:19:47,733
That's too much, Hazel.

341
00:19:47,867 --> 00:19:51,733
That still needs approval, and
it's way past banking hours.

342
00:19:51,867 --> 00:19:53,400
I don't care.

343
00:19:53,533 --> 00:19:56,133
Figure it out.

344
00:19:56,267 --> 00:19:58,467
If you don't, you choose.

345
00:19:58,600 --> 00:20:00,367
I'll kill this woman.

346
00:20:00,500 --> 00:20:03,433
Felma's life or the thing
I'm demanding from you?

347
00:20:03,600 --> 00:20:06,900
Okay. We'll find a way
to meet your demands.

348
00:20:07,033 --> 00:20:09,833
But show us good faith.

349
00:20:09,967 --> 00:20:11,933
Let us speak to the hostage.

350
00:20:13,533 --> 00:20:15,467
You're being careful, huh?

351
00:20:15,600 --> 00:20:17,667
Fine.

352
00:20:17,800 --> 00:20:19,300
Stand up.

353
00:20:19,433 --> 00:20:20,667
Stand up!

354
00:20:29,833 --> 00:20:31,100
Come on!

355
00:20:38,700 --> 00:20:40,033
Hello.

356
00:20:41,367 --> 00:20:42,467
- Love!
- Mom!

357
00:20:42,600 --> 00:20:44,000
Mom!

358
00:20:46,700 --> 00:20:49,700
Felma, are you okay?

359
00:20:53,133 --> 00:20:54,933
So...

360
00:20:55,067 --> 00:20:57,200
was that enough proof of life?

361
00:20:58,467 --> 00:20:59,633
Thank you.

362
00:20:59,767 --> 00:21:04,833
Okay, do you need anything else
while we work on your demands?

363
00:21:04,967 --> 00:21:06,733
Food? Water?

364
00:21:07,700 --> 00:21:10,300
What am I, stupid?

365
00:21:10,467 --> 00:21:12,267
So you can poison me?

366
00:21:13,633 --> 00:21:15,733
We wouldn't do that, Hazel.

367
00:21:15,867 --> 00:21:20,133
If you want reassurance,
let Felma eat first.

368
00:21:21,167 --> 00:21:22,400
Fine.

369
00:21:22,533 --> 00:21:23,467
Okay.

370
00:21:23,600 --> 00:21:25,867
Call this number
if you need anything, okay?

371
00:21:26,000 --> 00:21:29,900
0918-941-9945.

372
00:21:33,433 --> 00:21:34,833
A helicopter and 20 million?

373
00:21:34,967 --> 00:21:36,200
Where are we supposed
to get that?

374
00:21:36,333 --> 00:21:37,933
Don't worry, Sir.

375
00:21:38,067 --> 00:21:40,900
We're not giving it to her.

376
00:21:41,033 --> 00:21:42,400
What do you mean?

377
00:21:42,567 --> 00:21:43,800
We have another plan.

378
00:21:45,967 --> 00:21:47,267
Colonel Sarabia.

379
00:21:49,067 --> 00:21:50,767
Ready for overwatch, Sir.

380
00:21:53,033 --> 00:21:54,133
Proceed.

381
00:21:58,433 --> 00:22:00,467
You sent in a sniper?

382
00:23:21,600 --> 00:23:23,800
No visual on the subject, Sir.

383
00:23:23,967 --> 00:23:28,533
Okay. If the suspect crosses
the threshold, call it out.

384
00:23:28,667 --> 00:23:31,100
Hold your fire until my command.

385
00:23:31,233 --> 00:23:34,233
Non-lethal shots authorized.

386
00:23:34,367 --> 00:23:37,800
Shoulder, arm, leg, copy?

387
00:23:37,933 --> 00:23:40,600
Kids, I got caught.

388
00:23:44,133 --> 00:23:47,200
Dad, why is there a sniper?

389
00:23:47,333 --> 00:23:49,233
Are they going to kill Hazel?

390
00:23:49,367 --> 00:23:51,833
No. You heard Colonel Sarabia,
right?

391
00:23:51,967 --> 00:23:53,267
They're going to shoot
in the safe zone.

392
00:23:53,400 --> 00:23:56,867
They'll target the shoulder,
leg, and arm.

393
00:23:57,033 --> 00:24:02,300
What if Mom's the one
who gets hit?

394
00:24:02,433 --> 00:24:03,500
Sister.

395
00:24:03,633 --> 00:24:05,133
Sis. Sis, don't cry.
Don't be scared.

396
00:24:05,267 --> 00:24:07,600
Be brave.

397
00:24:07,733 --> 00:24:09,900
It's Mom.

398
00:24:10,033 --> 00:24:12,233
Mom's the one who
gives me strength.

399
00:24:13,933 --> 00:24:16,133
I need Mom.

400
00:24:18,433 --> 00:24:20,867
Stop those negative thoughts.

401
00:24:43,833 --> 00:24:45,433
You have to be strong.

402
00:24:45,567 --> 00:24:47,233
Strong enough to fight
that demon.

403
00:24:47,367 --> 00:24:48,933
The suspect is moving.

404
00:24:49,067 --> 00:24:50,233
No clean angle.

405
00:24:50,367 --> 00:24:51,500
Hold your position.

406
00:24:51,633 --> 00:24:53,700
No shot unless I call it.

407
00:24:55,667 --> 00:24:56,800
Who did you take? Who's that?

408
00:24:56,933 --> 00:24:58,033
He's one of the men
who kidnapped me,

409
00:24:58,167 --> 00:25:02,100
and he's the one who helped
Hazel escape from prison!

410
00:25:02,267 --> 00:25:05,000
Where's the helicopter?
Where's my 20 million?

411
00:25:05,133 --> 00:25:07,067
We have six million so far.
We're still raising the rest.

412
00:25:07,200 --> 00:25:09,433
Hazel,
don't believe the Colonel!

413
00:25:09,567 --> 00:25:11,133
I know him! He's a liar!

414
00:25:11,267 --> 00:25:12,633
You fooled me!

415
00:25:12,767 --> 00:25:14,800
Put it on speaker!

416
00:25:14,933 --> 00:25:16,967
- You animal!
- Hazel, don't!

417
00:25:17,100 --> 00:25:19,167
- Hazel!
- Hazel, stop it!

418
00:25:19,300 --> 00:25:21,533
Don't hurt Felma!

419
00:25:21,667 --> 00:25:23,800
Hostage is
fighting back, Sir.

420
00:25:23,933 --> 00:25:25,567
I don't know
how to throw a punch,

421
00:25:25,700 --> 00:25:28,267
but this is what I can do!

422
00:25:28,400 --> 00:25:30,433
That's it! That's it, Mom!
Fight back!

423
00:25:30,567 --> 00:25:32,733
- You got this, Mom!
- Fight, girl!
